@startuml DigitalWellbeing_Annotated

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam ranksep 30
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam enum {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam interface {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

title <size:18>Digital Wellbeing System (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "User opens Instagram at 10am, closes at 10:30am. Session tracked. Stats show 2hr total today. Data persisted 7 days."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE
' ====================================================================
class DigitalWellbeingService <<Singleton>> {
    - {static} instance : DigitalWellbeingService
    - tracker : ScreenTimeTracker
    - statsService : UsageStatisticsService
    - retentionManager : DataRetentionManager
    - repository : UsageRepository
    - notificationService : NotificationService
    --
    + {static} getInstance() : DigitalWellbeingService
    + initialize() : void
    + onAppOpened(packageName) : void
    + onAppClosed(packageName) : void
    + getUsageStats() : UsageReport
    + getTodayScreenTime() : long
    + getTodayUsage(app) : DailyUsageSummary
    + getWeeklyReport() : UsageReport
    + setDailyLimit(app, minutes) : void
    + shutdown() : void
}

note top of DigitalWellbeingService #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "OS detects app open/close. Client calls
    DigitalWellbeingService — **Singleton + Facade**.
    Singleton because one tracker per device.
    Facade hides tracker, persistence, stats,
    retention behind one clean API."

    "Two key APIs:
    onAppOpened/Closed (write path)
    getUsageStats (read path)"
    **Patterns: Singleton + Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: CORE MODELS
' ====================================================================
class AppInfo {
    - packageName : String
    - displayName : String
    - category : AppCategory
    - iconPath : String
    --
    + getPackageName() : String
    + getDisplayName() : String
    + getCategory() : AppCategory
}

enum AppCategory {
    SOCIAL_MEDIA
    PRODUCTIVITY
    ENTERTAINMENT
    COMMUNICATION
    GAMING
    EDUCATION
    HEALTH
    OTHER
}

class UsageSession {
    - sessionId : String
    - app : AppInfo
    - startTime : long
    - endTime : long
    --
    + getDurationMillis() : long
    + getDurationMinutes() : int
    + isActive() : boolean
    + endSession(endTime) : void
}

class DailyUsageSummary {
    - date : LocalDate
    - app : AppInfo
    - totalTimeMillis : long
    - sessionCount : int
    - sessions : List<UsageSession>
    - firstOpened : LocalDateTime
    - lastClosed : LocalDateTime
    --
    + getTotalMinutes() : int
    + getTotalHours() : double
    + addSession(session) : void
    + getSessionCount() : int
}

note top of AppInfo #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - What are we tracking?**
    "Three core models, each with one job:"

    "**AppInfo** = which app (com.instagram,
    display name, category like SOCIAL_MEDIA).
    **UsageSession** = one open-to-close window.
    User opens Instagram at 10am, closes at
    10:30am — that's one 30-min session.
    **DailyUsageSummary** = all sessions of
    one app rolled up for one day.
    'Instagram: 2hr 15min today, 8 sessions.'"

    "Pure data. No business logic." **(SRP)**
end note

AppInfo --> AppCategory
UsageSession --> AppInfo : for app >
DailyUsageSummary --> AppInfo : per app >
DailyUsageSummary o-- UsageSession : aggregates >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: SCREEN TIME TRACKER (Singleton)
' ====================================================================
class ScreenTimeTracker {
    - activeSessions : Map<String, UsageSession>
    - observers : List<UsageEventObserver>
    --
    + onAppOpened(app) : void
    + onAppClosed(app) : void
    + getActiveSession(app) : UsageSession
    + getActiveSessions() : Map<String, UsageSession>
    + isAppActive(packageName) : boolean
    - createSession(app) : UsageSession
    - endSession(app) : UsageSession
    - notifyObservers(event) : void
}

class UsageEvent {
    - app : AppInfo
    - eventType : EventType
    - timestamp : long
    - session : UsageSession
    --
    + getApp() : AppInfo
    + getDuration() : long
}

enum EventType {
    APP_OPENED
    APP_CLOSED
    DAILY_LIMIT_REACHED
    SESSION_MILESTONE
}

note top of ScreenTimeTracker #BBDEFB
    **STEP 3 - The tracking engine.**
    "ScreenTimeTracker is the heart.
    onAppOpened('com.instagram') creates
    a new UsageSession with startTime=now.
    onAppClosed() ends the session,
    computes duration, and fires a
    UsageEvent to all observers."

    "activeSessions map tracks which apps
    are currently open. One user might have
    Instagram AND WhatsApp open simultaneously."
end note

ScreenTimeTracker --> UsageSession : creates >
ScreenTimeTracker --> UsageEvent : fires >
UsageEvent --> EventType
DigitalWellbeingService --> ScreenTimeTracker


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: OBSERVERS — Observer Pattern (KEY)
' ====================================================================
interface UsageEventObserver <<Observer>> {
    + onUsageEvent(event) : void
}

class PersistenceObserver <<ConcreteObserver>> {
    - repository : UsageRepository
    --
    + onUsageEvent(event) : void
}

class StatisticsUpdateObserver <<ConcreteObserver>> {
    - statsService : UsageStatisticsService
    --
    + onUsageEvent(event) : void
}

class UsageLimitObserver <<ConcreteObserver>> {
    - dailyLimits : Map<String, Integer>
    - currentUsage : Map<String, Long>
    - notificationService : NotificationService
    --
    + onUsageEvent(event) : void
    + setDailyLimit(app, minutes) : void
    - checkLimit(app) : void
}

class CategoryTrackerObserver <<ConcreteObserver>> {
    - categoryUsage : Map<AppCategory, Long>
    --
    + onUsageEvent(event) : void
    + getCategoryBreakdown() : Map<AppCategory, Long>
}

note top of UsageEventObserver #FFE0B2
    **STEP 4 - Session ends. Now what? (KEY STEP)**
    "When user closes an app, multiple things
    must happen. But the tracker should NOT
    know about persistence, stats, or limits."

    "**Observer Pattern** — tracker fires event,
    4 observers react independently:"

    "1. **PersistenceObserver** -> saves to storage
    2. **StatisticsObserver** -> refreshes live stats
    3. **LimitObserver** -> checks if daily cap hit,
       alerts user '2hr Instagram limit reached!'
    4. **CategoryTracker** -> updates per-category totals"

    "Want parental controls? Add one observer.
    Tracker code NEVER changes." **(OCP)**
    **Pattern: Observer | OCP, SRP**
end note

UsageEventObserver <|.. PersistenceObserver
UsageEventObserver <|.. StatisticsUpdateObserver
UsageEventObserver <|.. UsageLimitObserver
UsageEventObserver <|.. CategoryTrackerObserver
ScreenTimeTracker --> UsageEventObserver : notifies >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: PERSISTENCE — Repository + Strategy (KEY)
' ====================================================================
interface UsageRepository <<Repository>> {
    + saveSession(session) : void
    + getSessions(app, date) : List<UsageSession>
    + getDailySummary(app, date) : DailyUsageSummary
    + getAllSummaries(startDate, endDate) : List<DailyUsageSummary>
    + deleteOlderThan(date) : void
    + getTotalScreenTime(date) : long
}

class UsageRepositoryImpl {
    - persistenceStrategy : PersistenceStrategy
    --
    + saveSession(session) : void
    + getSessions(app, date) : List<UsageSession>
    + getDailySummary(app, date) : DailyUsageSummary
    + getAllSummaries(startDate, endDate) : List<DailyUsageSummary>
    + deleteOlderThan(date) : void
}

interface PersistenceStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + write(key, data) : void
    + read(key) : String
    + delete(key) : void
    + readRange(prefix, startKey, endKey) : List<String>
}

class SQLitePersistenceStrategy {
    - databasePath : String
    --
    + write(key, data) : void
    + read(key) : String
    + delete(key) : void
    + readRange(prefix, startKey, endKey) : List<String>
}

class FilePersistenceStrategy {
    - baseDirectory : String
    --
    + write(key, data) : void
    + read(key) : String
    + delete(key) : void
    + readRange(prefix, startKey, endKey) : List<String>
}

class SharedPrefsPersistenceStrategy {
    - prefsName : String
    --
    + write(key, data) : void
    + read(key) : String
    + delete(key) : void
    + readRange(prefix, startKey, endKey) : List<String>
}

class InMemoryPersistenceStrategy {
    - store : Map<String, String>
    --
    + write(key, data) : void
    + read(key) : String
    + delete(key) : void
    + readRange(prefix, startKey, endKey) : List<String>
}

note top of UsageRepository #FFCDD2
    **STEP 5 - Where does data go? (KEY STEP)**
    "Requirement: persist across device reboots.
    Two patterns work together:"

    "**Repository Pattern** — business logic calls
    saveSession(). It NEVER knows if data goes
    to SQLite, file, or cloud. **(DIP)**"

    "**Strategy Pattern** — storage backend is
    swappable at construction time:
    **SQLite** for production (structured queries).
    **File** for debugging/export.
    **SharedPrefs** for lightweight config.
    **InMemory** for unit tests (no disk I/O)."

    "New storage (CloudSync)? One new class.
    Nothing else changes." **(OCP, LSP)**
    **Patterns: Repository + Strategy | DIP, OCP, LSP**
end note

UsageRepository <|.. UsageRepositoryImpl
UsageRepositoryImpl --> PersistenceStrategy : delegates >
PersistenceStrategy <|.. SQLitePersistenceStrategy
PersistenceStrategy <|.. FilePersistenceStrategy
PersistenceStrategy <|.. SharedPrefsPersistenceStrategy
PersistenceStrategy <|.. InMemoryPersistenceStrategy
PersistenceObserver --> UsageRepository : saves via >
DigitalWellbeingService --> UsageRepository


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: STATISTICS + BUILDER
' ====================================================================
class UsageStatisticsService {
    - repository : UsageRepository
    --
    + getTodayUsage(app) : DailyUsageSummary
    + getTotalScreenTime(date) : long
    + getWeeklyReport() : UsageReport
    + getMostUsedApps(days, limit) : List<DailyUsageSummary>
    + getAverageDailyUsage(app, days) : int
    + getCategoryBreakdown(date) : Map<AppCategory, Long>
    + getUsageTrend(app, days) : List<DailyUsageSummary>
}

class UsageReportBuilder <<Builder>> {
    - startDate : LocalDate
    - endDate : LocalDate
    - summaries : List<DailyUsageSummary>
    - totalScreenTime : long
    --
    + setDateRange(start, end) : UsageReportBuilder
    + addDailySummary(summary) : UsageReportBuilder
    + build() : UsageReport
}

class UsageReport {
    - startDate : LocalDate
    - endDate : LocalDate
    - dailySummaries : List<DailyUsageSummary>
    - totalScreenTimeMillis : long
    - appBreakdown : Map<String, Long>
    - categoryBreakdown : Map<AppCategory, Long>
    - mostUsedApp : AppInfo
    - averageDailyMinutes : int
    --
    + getTotalHours() : double
    + getDailyAverage() : double
    + getAppBreakdown() : Map<String, Long>
    + getCategoryBreakdown() : Map<AppCategory, Long>
    + getMostUsedApp() : AppInfo
}

note top of UsageReportBuilder #D1C4E9
    **STEP 6 - Display usage statistics.**
    "User opens 'Screen Time' to see weekly report.
    UsageStatisticsService reads from repository."

    "**Builder Pattern** — UsageReport has 8+ fields
    (date range, summaries, totals, breakdown,
    most used app, averages). Builder constructs
    it step by step:"

    "builder.setDateRange(mon, sun)
      .addDailySummary(monSummary)
      .addDailySummary(tueSummary)
      ...
      .build() // computes totals + averages"

    "Service queries data. Builder constructs.
    Report is immutable." **(SRP)**
    **Pattern: Builder | SRP**
end note

UsageStatisticsService --> UsageReportBuilder : uses >
UsageReportBuilder --> UsageReport : builds >
UsageStatisticsService --> UsageRepository : reads from >
StatisticsUpdateObserver --> UsageStatisticsService : refreshes >
DigitalWellbeingService --> UsageStatisticsService


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: DATA RETENTION — 7-Day Window
' ====================================================================
class DataRetentionManager {
    - repository : UsageRepository
    - retentionDays : int
    --
    + purgeExpiredData() : void
    + getRetentionWindow() : DateRange
    + isWithinRetention(date) : boolean
    + getRetentionDays() : int
}

class DateRange {
    - startDate : LocalDate
    - endDate : LocalDate
    --
    + contains(date) : boolean
    + getDayCount() : int
}

note top of DataRetentionManager #B2EBF2
    **STEP 7 - Keep only 7 days.**
    "Requirement: persist data for last 7 days.
    On every app startup, initialize() calls
    retentionManager.purgeExpiredData()
    which runs repo.deleteOlderThan(today - 7)."

    "Storage stays bounded. Change to 30 days?
    One field change." **(SRP)**

    "Data survives reboots because Step 5
    writes to durable storage (SQLite/file)."
end note

DataRetentionManager --> DateRange : defines window >
DataRetentionManager --> UsageRepository : cleans >
DigitalWellbeingService --> DataRetentionManager


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: NOTIFICATION — Strategy
' ====================================================================
class NotificationService {
    - strategies : List<NotificationStrategy>
    --
    + notifyLimitReached(app, limit) : void
    + notifyDailySummary(report) : void
}

interface NotificationStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + send(title, message) : void
}

class SystemNotification {
    + send(title, message) : void
}

class InAppToast {
    + send(title, message) : void
}

class SilentLog {
    + send(title, message) : void
}

note bottom of NotificationStrategy #B2EBF2
    **STEP 8 - Alert the user.**
    "UsageLimitObserver detects '2hr Instagram
    limit reached'. Notifies user via
    **Strategy Pattern**: system notification,
    in-app toast, or silent log."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP**
end note

NotificationStrategy <|.. SystemNotification
NotificationStrategy <|.. InAppToast
NotificationStrategy <|.. SilentLog
NotificationService --> NotificationStrategy : delegates >
UsageLimitObserver --> NotificationService : alerts via >
DigitalWellbeingService --> NotificationService


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "User opens Instagram -> DigitalWellbeingService
    delegates to ScreenTimeTracker -> tracker creates UsageSession.
    User closes -> session ends, UsageEvent fired -> 4 **Observers**
    react: PersistenceObserver saves via **Repository + Strategy**
    (SQLite survives reboots), StatisticsObserver refreshes stats,
    LimitObserver checks cap, CategoryTracker updates breakdown.
    User checks screen time -> **Builder** constructs UsageReport.
    On startup -> DataRetentionManager purges data older than 7 days.
    6 patterns: **Singleton, Facade, Observer, Repository, Strategy (x2), Builder**.
    All 3 requirements met."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= SOLID |
    | 1 | OS detects app open/close, calls DigitalWellbeingService | Singleton + Facade | SRP, DIP |
    | 2 | AppInfo, UsageSession (one open-close), DailyUsageSummary (per day) | -- | SRP |
    | 3 | Tracker creates session on open, ends on close, fires event | -- | SRP |
    | 4 | Observers: persist, refresh stats, check limit, track category | Observer | OCP, SRP |
    | 5 | Repository abstracts storage. Strategy swaps SQLite/File/InMemory | Repository + Strategy | DIP, OCP, LSP |
    | 6 | Builder constructs weekly UsageReport step-by-step | Builder | SRP |
    | 7 | On startup, purge data older than 7 days | -- | SRP |
    | 8 | Alert user when daily limit reached (system notif / toast) | Strategy | OCP |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Req: Track screen time** = Steps 2-4 | **Req: Display stats** = Step 6 | **Req: Persist 7 days** = Steps 5+7 |  |
endlegend

@enduml
